I have been working on this issue and have written the c++ code for op.
I encountered the following error which i was unable to resolve.

  1. Upon accessing the 'i'th element of object of tensor class,using
    "object(i)"
    following error was shown:-
    error: no match for call to ‘(tensorflow::Tensor) (int&)’

2)Another one

tensorflow/core/framework/op_kernel.h: In member function ‘tensorflow::int64 tensorflow::PersistentTensor::AllocatedBytes() const’:
tensorflow/core/framework/op_kernel.h:210:49: error: ‘const class tensorflow::Tensor’ has no member named ‘AllocatedBytes’
   int64 AllocatedBytes() const { return tensor_.AllocatedBytes(); }

This one is in the header file "op_kernel.h" itself.

I referenced this for adding the op.
Please help.

I have been working on this issue and have written the c++ code for op.
I encountered the following error which i was unable to resolve.

1) Upon accessing the 'i'th element of object of tensor class,using
"object(i)"
following error was shown:-
**error: no match for call to ‘(tensorflow::Tensor) (int&)’**

2)Another one
```
tensorflow/core/framework/op_kernel.h: In member function ‘tensorflow::int64 tensorflow::PersistentTensor::AllocatedBytes() const’:
tensorflow/core/framework/op_kernel.h:210:49: error: ‘const class tensorflow::Tensor’ has no member named ‘AllocatedBytes’
   int64 AllocatedBytes() const { return tensor_.AllocatedBytes(); }
```
This one is in the header file "op_kernel.h" itself.

I referenced [this](https://www.tensorflow.org/extend/adding_an_op) for adding the op.
Please help.
